1
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,702
- Are they dead?
- Yeah, let's go.

2
00:03:51,620 --> 00:03:54,100
- The horses! Where are the horses?

3
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,944
- Look, Mantas! Here they come!

4
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:28,424
Let go.

5
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:10,506
I Am Sartana...
Trade Your Guns for a Coffin!

6
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:27,142
Hi, Burt.
How are you?

7
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:33,189
I was after you for a long time.

8
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:22,427
3000.

9
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,581
4000.

10
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:25,185
5000.

11
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,661
Not so fast.
I want to check first.

12
00:07:34,380 --> 00:07:35,427
That's him.

13
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,508
Going for poker game, right?

14
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:41,628
Why should I refuse myself?

15
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:44,869
I have to invest money somewhere.

16
00:07:56,420 --> 00:07:57,660
Wake up, buddy.

17
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:01,225
I want to buy your clothes.

18
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:05,466
That's enough?

19
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:07,624
Hey, Sartana!

20
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:10,181
- This is your investment?
- Yes.

21
00:08:58,380 --> 00:09:00,826
Where the hell are you going?
Can't you read?

22
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:02,061
THIS IS THE VILLAGE CEMETARY

23
00:09:02,220 --> 00:09:04,621
STRANGERS DO NOT ENTER!
OR DIE!!

24
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:09,140
What it will be then?

25
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:16,584
What do you want?

26
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:18,908
Whiskey, tequila,
something to eat?

27
00:10:21,540 --> 00:10:22,666
Tell me something.

28
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:24,701
Who loves gold here?
Mantas?

29
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,942
I think, everyone loves the gold.

30
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:31,543
The gold diggers love the most.

31
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,340
And there are many who look for it.

32
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:34,468
Yes?

33
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:36,748
Hey, peasant!

34
00:10:38,900 --> 00:10:40,470
Yes, you!.

35
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:45,307
Do not stick your nose in other people business.

36
00:10:58,260 --> 00:11:00,581
Do you recognize this bag?

37
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:03,788
And what is that to you?

38
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,550
Are you looking for this?

39
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:29,671
You're in troubles!

40
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:33,188
It was Dead Eye Golfay.
He will not forget this!

41
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:36,588
Really.
I didn't know.

42
00:11:39,260 --> 00:11:40,989
Do not worry.

43
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,109
Bring me something to eat.

44
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:45,181
I love eggs.

45
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:46,580
Make sure they're fresh.

46
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:04,945
What happened?

47
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,621
Golfay, you fell into the soup?

48
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:12,590
Don't laugh.

49
00:12:14,060 --> 00:12:16,301
What did you eat?
Youy beard full of beans!

50
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:22,345
Shut the fuck up, stupid idiots!

51
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,743
I met one hombre who knows about the gold.

52
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,470
And he was asking for Mantas.

53
00:12:29,980 --> 00:12:31,345
Damn it!

54
00:12:33,740 --> 00:12:36,027
Paco, get Mantas.

55
00:12:36,180 --> 00:12:37,784
Golfay! Go to the inn!

56
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:39,908
Sereno, Miguel, go with him.

57
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:41,630
The rest to the windows.

58
00:12:48,140 --> 00:12:49,824
You stay quiet, understand?

59
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:53,824
Mantas asked to look after you!

60
00:13:23,580 --> 00:13:25,230
You like them well cooked?

61
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:28,345
Yes, but hurry or I'll starve to death.

62
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,707
You'll die but not from hunger!

63
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:35,621
IIt seems he came back
for some more soup.

64
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:11,908
I never seen it before.
How do you call this?

65
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:14,150
Sandwich colt.

66
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:16,628
I hope they'll shot the gringo.

67
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:18,624
It would be the best.

68
00:14:19,620 --> 00:14:20,621
Look!

69
00:14:20,940 --> 00:14:22,226
They are coming!

70
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,022
Put them as far as you can from here.

71
00:14:49,660 --> 00:14:50,468
Wait.

72
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:54,389
That is exactly what that bastard
expects us to do!

73
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:58,226
We will stay here till
Mantas is back.

74
00:15:03,540 --> 00:15:04,951
Where's the kid?

75
00:15:06,860 --> 00:15:08,066
Emiliano!

76
00:15:16,380 --> 00:15:18,906
You should not have done it Maldida.

77
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:20,710
You'll be sorry!

78
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:24,785
Mantas will kill you.

79
00:15:27,620 --> 00:15:29,702
Hey, wait a minute! Watch out!

80
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:56,945
It's all the money I have, senor.

81
00:15:57,180 --> 00:15:59,387
I give them to you to save my mother.

82
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:04,228
Where is she?

83
00:16:05,060 --> 00:16:07,062
In that opposite house, senor.

84
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:09,867
And kill all the men, they're bandits.

85
00:16:14,940 --> 00:16:17,261
It's wrong to pay a man to kill someone.

86
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:22,660
What is he waiting for?

87
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:44,660
Salute!

88
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:57,590
Oh boy, surely defeat.

89
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,943
It's because of yours very good whiskey.

90
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,465
Obviously, yes.

91
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:06,748
Do you think our friends
started to be nervous?

92
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:08,830
I would say they're furious.

93
00:17:10,820 --> 00:17:11,901
Fine.

94
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:13,710
In this case, I'm going.

95
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,706
Anyway, I'd like to know
if Mantas coming here?

96
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:26,670
I see him pretty much every day...

97
00:17:26,820 --> 00:17:29,187
... but they never talk about their plans.

98
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:30,866
I believe you.

99
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:32,466
I got scared. There was such a shoot out.

100
00:18:34,740 --> 00:18:36,185
I'm not an expert ...

101
00:18:36,420 --> 00:18:40,027
...but now I'll see for a first time.

102
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:42,308
One man against four Mantas' guys?

103
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:46,260
I'm not going to attack anyone,
only use them a little.

104
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:51,262
Someone may get hurt
if it's not moving fast enough.

105
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,911
<i> Hey, you there!</i>

106
00:18:59,940 --> 00:19:00,748
<i> Can you hear me? </i>

107
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:05,190
<i> Come out, slowly. </i>

108
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:07,502
<i> Have a little talk.</i>

109
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:10,347
<i>You hear me?</i>

110
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:14,070
<i> Let's talk but don't be silly...</i>

111
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,501
<i>... or I'm going to blow up the house.</i>

112
00:19:18,660 --> 00:19:22,301
<i>You have 5 seconds.
Can you hear me better now?</i>

113
00:19:24,740 --> 00:19:26,105
<i>Are you decided?</i>

114
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:36,060
Out!

115
00:19:45,740 --> 00:19:46,548
<i> Sorry hombres...</ i>

116
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:47,981
<i>...but I'm here. </ i>

117
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,261
Mom!

118
00:20:17,540 --> 00:20:18,587
Thank you.

119
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:21,789
God bless you!
They kept me prisoner.

120
00:20:21,940 --> 00:20:24,147
Be thankful to the child.

121
00:20:25,940 --> 00:20:28,102
They kept you here for a long time?

122
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:31,104
Have you heard them talking about the gold?

123
00:20:31,260 --> 00:20:32,261
Yes.

124
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,990
They often spoke about certain place.

125
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:37,223
I think it's called Appaloosa,
but I do not know where it is.

126
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:40,068
I'm afraid I did not help you much with that.

127
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:41,991
Light?

128
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:46,707
Thank you.

129
00:20:47,460 --> 00:20:50,987
Do not worry, ma'am,
I'll find something.

130
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:54,586
Dynamite.

131
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,186
Dynamite ...

132
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:00,783
God bless you.

133
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:05,031
Now we can go back to our farm.
They will never find us.

134
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:06,631
Good luck.

135
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,143
How much do I owe you for the eggs?

136
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:23,263
On the house.

137
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,150
I was never so entertained.

138
00:21:25,580 --> 00:21:26,945
Thank you.

139
00:21:27,340 --> 00:21:30,264
Cetendroit looks like a cemetery.

140
00:21:30,620 --> 00:21:31,860
Before, it was different.

141
00:21:32,180 --> 00:21:34,831
Then Mantas took control of our town.

142
00:21:34,980 --> 00:21:36,584
I guess I'm stuck here forever.

143
00:21:36,980 --> 00:21:39,028
Where are you going, amigo?

144
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:42,864
After Right Place.

145
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:32,421
Another mercenary
who wants to work for Mr Spencer.

146
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:34,582
Quit whining!

147
00:22:34,740 --> 00:22:37,141
I don't think it's a reason he's here.

148
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:38,790
What happens there, Trixie?

149
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:43,586
Is there something interesting on the street?

150
00:22:45,820 --> 00:22:47,231
Not really...

151
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:49,703
Just a stranger.

152
00:22:51,300 --> 00:22:53,667
One of those
who are paid by Spencer.

153
00:22:55,020 --> 00:22:56,226
Ask him, Hoagy.

154
00:22:57,540 --> 00:23:00,384
Here, Baxter, Mr. Baxter ...

155
00:23:00,540 --> 00:23:02,269
Apropos our gold ...

156
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:05,105
We learned that the cargo
had not arrived.

157
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:07,786
Mr. Spencer received the news this morning.

158
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:09,704
Surely bandits again
attacked the shipment.

159
00:23:09,860 --> 00:23:13,990
Spencer spent a lot of money
to pay for the escort.

160
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:17,269
Now, he is going to pay for the funerals.

161
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:19,744
Next time all will be OK.

162
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:24,461
Tell your friends, the next
delivery will start on Monday morning.

163
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:28,261
But we lost three in a row, Mr. Baxter.

164
00:23:28,420 --> 00:23:30,502
This time, we will be fine.

165
00:23:30,660 --> 00:23:33,550
Mr. Spencer has a plan.

166
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:34,986
You'll see.

167
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:37,548
Good afternoon.

168
00:23:46,220 --> 00:23:47,301
Who's in charge?

169
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:51,026
What do you want?

170
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:54,348
I'd like to get a room.

171
00:23:54,580 --> 00:23:57,902
I oughta warn you. The beds are full of bedbugs and uncomfortable, too.

172
00:23:58,060 --> 00:24:00,984
We ain't got roulette, there's no floorshow,
and there's no girls.

173
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:03,142
Our main activity is keeping out of the graveyard.

174
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:05,746
I like quiet places, ma'am.

175
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:13,507
If you do not work
for Spencer, I have a room.

176
00:24:15,140 --> 00:24:16,824
I'm sorry ...

177
00:24:19,660 --> 00:24:22,550
Goodbye, Trixie.
I greet Spencer from you.

178
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:30,584
Very rude guy.

179
00:27:17,300 --> 00:27:18,108
Emiliano!

180
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:27,870
Hey, Mantas! It's me!

181
00:27:30,500 --> 00:27:32,502
Where are the rest?
Let's go, search for them!

182
00:27:33,020 --> 00:27:34,067
Hurry!

183
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:37,748
Mantas, they're all dead!

184
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:40,941
Find the old man!

185
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:48,347
I did not do anything!

186
00:27:49,540 --> 00:27:52,350
Come on, Mantas wants to talk to you!

187
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:55,231
I did not do anything! Let me go!

188
00:27:55,500 --> 00:27:57,821
You bastard! Tell me who did it?

189
00:27:57,980 --> 00:27:59,186
I've done nothing.

190
00:27:59,340 --> 00:28:03,061
It's your fault our friends are dead.

191
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:05,462
You're gonna pay.
It's all your fault.

192
00:28:05,620 --> 00:28:07,987
Bastard! Where is my wife?

193
00:28:10,940 --> 00:28:12,385
Maldida not here! She's gone.

194
00:28:13,300 --> 00:28:15,587
I don't know anything!
Where did she go?

195
00:28:15,740 --> 00:28:16,980
I know nothing.

196
00:28:17,140 --> 00:28:18,744
You helped the gringo, right?

197
00:28:18,980 --> 00:28:20,869
I wasn't helping anyone, I swear.

198
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:25,184
Where is a women? Speak!
I gonna kill you!

199
00:28:25,340 --> 00:28:26,501
Speak!

200
00:28:26,740 --> 00:28:29,391
Please, Mantas.
Please!

201
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:34,350
Damn gringo!

202
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,310
He killed seven of my men.
Seven!

203
00:28:37,460 --> 00:28:39,622
And my women is gone!

204
00:28:40,300 --> 00:28:41,631
He fooled Mantas.

205
00:28:42,380 --> 00:28:44,462
He's a smart guy.

206
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:48,307
Yes. A gringo who
thinks with his head.

207
00:28:49,220 --> 00:28:50,904
He mocked us.

208
00:28:51,260 --> 00:28:52,785
He butchered our companieros.

209
00:28:58,700 --> 00:28:59,587
Do you understand?

210
00:29:00,140 --> 00:29:02,427
He is very dangerous!

211
00:29:04,540 --> 00:29:06,224
We must be careful.

212
00:29:09,660 --> 00:29:12,869
Who is this gringo?

213
00:29:16,820 --> 00:29:18,345
Is he faster than me?

214
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:27,870
Faster than me?

215
00:29:29,380 --> 00:29:31,906
I'm not going to waste my time on you.

216
00:29:32,060 --> 00:29:34,427
Where did he go, you filthy worm?

217
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:35,940
Appaloosa.

218
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:37,545
Damn.

219
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:40,747
The only hometown I can not go.

220
00:29:41,180 --> 00:29:44,024
Augustine, Machete, Antonio!
Go ahead.

221
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:48,106
Wait!

222
00:29:48,580 --> 00:29:52,744
This gringo is fast.
He killed our friends.

223
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:54,751
Be careful.

224
00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:56,910
You are like sons to me.

225
00:29:57,300 --> 00:29:58,347
Quick, you bastards!

226
00:29:58,740 --> 00:30:00,310
Move your asses!

227
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:30,742
Two pounds, three ounces. Right?

228
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:33,062
If you say so, Mr. Spencer ...

229
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:38,861
Here you go.

230
00:30:39,540 --> 00:30:40,587
You OK with this?

231
00:30:41,420 --> 00:30:42,467
...
I'm sorry.

232
00:30:44,340 --> 00:30:46,547
And you.
Isn't it a gold in your purse?

233
00:30:47,820 --> 00:30:51,586
I worked like a dog for six months.
I do not want to lose my money.

234
00:30:52,220 --> 00:30:53,585
I do not force anyone.

235
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:58,704
I was just doing you a favor
buying gold from you.

236
00:31:01,300 --> 00:31:03,223
Naturally, Mr. Spencer.

237
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:05,629
Do not worry, Tornovsky.

238
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:08,501
The gold will be delivered this time, I promise.

239
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:12,381
Maybe, if I pay you some money up front.

240
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:15,064
Say 50 dollars.

241
00:31:15,420 --> 00:31:16,865
But this are two pounds!

242
00:31:17,300 --> 00:31:18,984
You are not stupid man...

243
00:31:21,300 --> 00:31:24,907
I thought you'll accept what I'd offer.

244
00:31:45,380 --> 00:31:46,586
Hey, amigo!

245
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:49,183
Could you make me some eggs?
I want to eat.

246
00:31:49,420 --> 00:31:51,991
Call me Angelo. One
or two eggs do you want?

247
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:53,266
One, Angelo.

248
00:31:53,500 --> 00:31:55,741
Do not know that the eggs
are not good for the digestion?

249
00:32:20,780 --> 00:32:21,941
Stand up!

250
00:32:22,380 --> 00:32:24,951
Hold your hands
away from the bread!

251
00:32:30,780 --> 00:32:33,226
And do not try to trick me!

252
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:34,950
Step away from the table!

253
00:32:36,540 --> 00:32:37,780
OK?

254
00:32:38,260 --> 00:32:41,150
Count to three, and then...

255
00:32:46,100 --> 00:32:46,908
One

256
00:32:51,380 --> 00:32:52,347
Two.

257
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:08,504
It all happened so suddenly.

258
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:14,267
I just washed the floor this morning.

259
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:17,427
I hope there will be many visitors.

260
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:18,786
I hope so too.

261
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:21,031
Where's the sheriff's office?

262
00:33:21,180 --> 00:33:22,864
No sheriff, and we do not need it.

263
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:24,790
This city is run by just one man.

264
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:27,229
In other words Mr. Spencer.

265
00:33:27,500 --> 00:33:29,502
Mr. Spencer...

266
00:33:30,260 --> 00:33:31,307
Fine.

267
00:33:32,340 --> 00:33:33,501
I think I need to talk to him.

268
00:33:48,420 --> 00:33:49,910
Oh, what a surprise!
Glamorous.

269
00:34:00,860 --> 00:34:03,022
You came to kiss me on the hand?

270
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:07,708
Can I come in?

271
