trying to pull out the gun.

278
00:34:52,580 --> 00:34:54,662
- But I do not ...
- Do you mind?

279
00:34:56,380 --> 00:34:57,791
Go back to sleep.

280
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:05,670
I'm sorry.
Baxter is a violent man.

281
00:35:06,020 --> 00:35:08,466
But you must be tough around here.

282
00:35:08,620 --> 00:35:12,386
There were three Mexicans in the saloon
trying to shoot me.

283
00:35:13,260 --> 00:35:15,103
I'm afraid their idea went wrong.

284
00:35:15,860 --> 00:35:17,464
One, however, looked very familiar.

285
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:22,145
May I ask why
are you telling me this story?

286
00:35:23,140 --> 00:35:27,190
Your shipment of gold has been kidnapped

287
00:35:27,740 --> 00:35:30,823
These three men
were among robbers.

288
00:35:30,980 --> 00:35:34,541
Part of this gold was mine.
I pay for everything.

289
00:35:35,380 --> 00:35:38,782
The transport, the guards and I pay
the miners as well.

290
00:35:40,700 --> 00:35:43,431
How you could stay aside
to what was happening?

291
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:46,664
I couldn't do anything.

292
00:35:46,940 --> 00:35:48,863
I was too far.

293
00:35:49,340 --> 00:35:51,468
You did not try to stop them?

294
00:35:52,900 --> 00:35:54,140
Free?

295
00:35:54,300 --> 00:35:56,826
Nobody gets into trouble
for nothing.

296
00:35:57,060 --> 00:35:58,630
But if you do not mind to pay me.

297
00:35:59,780 --> 00:36:02,226
I can escort the next convoy.

298
00:36:02,900 --> 00:36:04,982
Give me a day or two to
think, Mr. Sartana.

299
00:36:05,220 --> 00:36:07,587
Think about it, Mr. Spencer.

300
00:36:09,380 --> 00:36:11,462
But do not think too much about it.

301
00:36:12,180 --> 00:36:14,342
I already sent for
two competent guys.

302
00:36:14,500 --> 00:36:16,821
I hope they do better their jobs then...

303
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:18,903
...Travis, for example.

304
00:36:19,060 --> 00:36:20,471
I do not know him.

305
00:36:22,660 --> 00:36:24,981
Travis was recently hired by you.

306
00:36:25,460 --> 00:36:29,101
I guess he was using fake name.

307
00:36:29,380 --> 00:36:32,031
He preferred to still the gold
instead of to convoy.

308
00:36:32,260 --> 00:36:34,388
Well, you know where to find me.

309
00:36:43,500 --> 00:36:44,308
More.

310
00:36:44,820 --> 00:36:46,106
Big whiskey is a dollar

311
00:36:53,300 --> 00:36:55,667
So Trixie, what do we do?

312
00:36:56,180 --> 00:36:57,591
To you, ma'am.

313
00:36:57,940 --> 00:37:00,511
I'm not in charge here.
I don't know.

314
00:37:00,660 --> 00:37:01,991
<i>You should talk to him.</i>

315
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:06,582
Tell me, Angelo.
What happens here at night?

316
00:37:06,940 --> 00:37:10,069
Most evenings we drink,
then we go to sleep.

317
00:37:10,340 --> 00:37:11,580
This sounds very exciting...

318
00:37:11,740 --> 00:37:13,424
Mr. Sartana!

319
00:37:45,460 --> 00:37:47,428
Mr. Spencer wants us to be friends.

320
00:37:50,020 --> 00:37:52,148
Mr. Spencer is a smart man.

321
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:54,746
He doesn't want
to pay for your funeral.

322
