Fantastic.

540
00:56:27,620 --> 00:56:30,703
It was a bluff, or perhaps both.
Is not it?

541
00:56:31,020 --> 00:56:32,226
Who knows?

542
00:56:32,380 --> 00:56:34,826
If you want to know
you have to pay.

543
00:56:35,180 --> 00:56:36,705
Quite a lot.

544
00:56:37,820 --> 00:56:40,266
$10,000.00 seems reasonable.

545
00:56:40,980 --> 00:56:43,711
And your gold convoy
reaches the destination.

546
00:56:48,220 --> 00:56:51,508
The word "Trust" does not seem
to exist in your vocabulary.

547
00:56:51,740 --> 00:56:55,790
I trust everyone only
on 50 percent.

548
00:56:57,060 --> 00:56:59,222
I was expecting this.

549
00:57:06,020 --> 00:57:08,751
Why did you chose me
over Sartana?

550
00:57:08,980 --> 00:57:10,220
You won at the poker.

551
00:57:11,820 --> 00:57:13,231
This is a good reason.

552
00:57:17,140 --> 00:57:18,869
You can come out.

553
00:57:20,300 --> 00:57:22,029
Very good acting.

554
00:57:22,340 --> 00:57:24,502
You think that Sabata was also a fool.

555
00:57:25,740 --> 00:57:27,629
No matter now.

556
00:57:28,100 --> 00:57:30,990
He played this game with us,

557
00:57:31,140 --> 00:57:32,824
because he expected
to win. Do you agree?

558
00:57:33,060 --> 00:57:35,461
All this is well guessed, Mr. Spencer.

559
00:57:35,620 --> 00:57:38,942
You understand that Sabata
wasn't here by accident.

560
00:57:39,100 --> 00:57:42,547
Mantas and his
gang also run for their money.

561
00:57:43,260 --> 00:57:44,068
By the way...

562
00:57:44,820 --> 00:57:45,628
What did you tell Baxter?

563
00:57:45,780 --> 00:57:47,908
I have no reason to tell him anything.

564
00:57:48,660 --> 00:57:50,264
Perfect plan.

565
00:57:50,500 --> 00:57:52,582
It is necessary to divide the enemy.

566
00:57:53,260 --> 00:57:55,262
Sabata is killing bandits ...

567
00:57:55,420 --> 00:57:56,751
And I kill Sabata.

568
00:57:57,220 --> 00:57:58,551
This is clear.

569
00:57:58,860 --> 00:58:02,148
If the gold was with me
and not here, it would be in bigger danger.

570
00:58:02,300 --> 00:58:03,870
Beautiful safe, though.

571
00:58:04,020 --> 00:58:05,863
It's the best.

572
00:58:06,140 --> 00:58:08,427
The Galagher manufactured specifically for me.

573
00:58:09,140 --> 00:58:10,346
I do not regret the money...

574
00:58:10,500 --> 00:58:13,743
...when it comes to protecting the gold,
the miners sweated for.

575
00:58:15,420 --> 00:58:18,185
Unfortunately, only a few likes you.

576
00:58:27,340 --> 00:58:29,263
Pair of aces. I won.

577
00:58:30,300 --> 00:58:32,621
Let's see. I owe you ...

578
00:58:36,140 --> 00:58:37,471
One million three hundred thousand...

579
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:41,029
Four hundred and seventy dollars.

580
00:58:45,060 --> 00:58:47,347
...and 50 cents.

581
00:58:47,740 --> 00:58:49,822
You tried to deceive me, Angelo?

582
00:58:53,140 --> 00:58:54,744
Well. I'm going to bed.

583
00:58:56,300 --> 00:58:58,302
Good night, sir.

584
00:59:03,420 --> 00:59:05,741
You got the wrong room.

585
00:59:05,980 --> 00:59:07,345
No.

586
00:59:08,740 --> 00:59:09,821
I want to talk to you.

587
00:59:11,540 --> 00:59:14,862
I get the feeling that the conversation
with the gun can be quite noisy.

588
00:59:15,020 --> 00:59:17,227
It will not be...

589
00:59:18,660 --> 00:59:20,503
...if you do what I say.

590
00:59:26,220 --> 00:59:27,665
I am afraid that the
gun is not loaded.

591
00:59:28,300 --> 00:59:29,904
You' don't understand.

592
00:59:30,260 --> 00:59:32,308
I only want to talk business.

593
00:59:34,140 --> 00:59:34,948
For now.

594
00:59:36,020 --> 00:59:37,181
Pity.

595
00:59:37,700 --> 00:59:38,940
I'm listening.

596
00:59:39,100 --> 00:59:42,388
When I first came here, I thought
Appaloosa will be growing city.

597
00:59:42,540 --> 00:59:46,101
I invested all my money
in the hotel and the bar.

598
00:59:46,380 --> 00:59:47,586
And all for nothing.

599
00:59:47,740 --> 00:59:48,741
Continue.

600
00:59:48,900 --> 00:59:52,222
The miners work for
the gold like animals.

601
00:59:52,700 --> 00:59:54,543
And those bandits steal everything.

602
00:59:54,860 --> 00:59:56,828
- You think it's just?
- No.

603
00:59:57,060 --> 01:00:00,189
They should spend it on you,
right?

604
01:00:00,420 --> 01:00:02,229
Yes, I want their money.

605
01:00:02,460 --> 01:00:05,464
If you steal the gold for me,
then I give you ...

606
01:00:06,500 --> 01:00:07,740
...let's say 10%.

607
01:00:07,980 --> 01:00:08,981
Okay?

608
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:11,781
I want 50%. I'm a pig.

609
01:00:14,020 --> 01:00:15,784
Do not look so sad. The small
income is better than nothing.

610
01:00:16,140 --> 01:00:19,189
I was wrong. I should rather talk to Sabata.

611
01:00:19,780 --> 01:00:23,148
What? With that coyote?
It would have taken everything.

612
01:00:27,780 --> 01:00:28,941
Bravo.

613
01:00:30,420 --> 01:00:33,629
But we do it my way.
Undress.

614
01:00:35,460 --> 01:00:36,791
You're doing it wrong.

615
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:40,702
I want everyone to think
I spent the night with you.

616
01:00:44,820 --> 01:00:47,061
There are a few things I need to do.

617
01:00:56,140 --> 01:00:58,984
To bad.
If it wasn't that damn gold...

618
01:03:28,060 --> 01:03:29,903
You never enter through the door?

619
01:03:30,860 --> 01:03:34,910
I wonder where you wonder at night
when a woman is waiting for you here.

620
01:03:35,420 --> 01:03:36,910
You did not take my place?

621
01:03:37,140 --> 01:03:38,710
I do not need to tie her up.

622
01:03:38,940 --> 01:03:40,271
I like you.

623
01:03:40,420 --> 01:03:42,263
But I do not her to be in
my way, when I'm working.

624
01:03:42,420 --> 01:03:45,469
I always knew
you were a professional.

625
01:03:46,300 --> 01:03:48,667
There will be no gold
in the coach tomorrow.

626
01:03:49,500 --> 01:03:51,264
Very clever. They want to beat me.

627
01:03:51,700 --> 01:03:54,180
They think I'm an idiot.

628
01:03:54,340 --> 01:03:56,024
Obviously.

629
01:03:56,340 --> 01:03:59,184
They think you were going to attack them,
as before.

630
01:03:59,900 --> 01:04:00,708
But if you do not...

631
01:04:01,700 --> 01:04:02,542
Then what?

632
01:04:03,100 --> 01:04:05,387
Romero, you will attack the convoy.

633
01:04:05,540 --> 01:04:07,304
With great pleasure.

634
01:04:08,580 --> 01:04:11,265
While I with the rest
go to town.

635
01:04:14,860 --> 01:04:17,181
This is the gringo idea.
The idea was that separate us.

636
01:04:17,340 --> 01:04:18,148
Good idea.

637
01:04:18,980 --> 01:04:20,982
But the other idea is mine,

638
01:04:21,380 --> 01:04:22,506
Sartana.

639
01:04:23,700 --> 01:04:25,782
I keep all the gold.

640
01:04:26,340 --> 01:04:28,741
And we share only among us.

641
01:04:29,100 --> 01:04:32,821
And if he comes and complains,
I'll kill him with my own hands.

642
01:05:08,740 --> 01:05:09,502
Baxter!

643
01:05:10,220 --> 01:05:11,665
Right, Mr. Spencer.

644
01:05:29,540 --> 01:05:32,987
You do not have to hurry, Baxter.
Plenty of time.

645
01:05:33,140 --> 01:05:37,464
Everyone else is working.
Mantas, Sartana, Sabata.

646
01:05:37,620 --> 01:05:39,349
All chase bags full of sand.

647
01:05:40,460 --> 01:05:41,871
Will anyone stay alive?

648
01:05:42,300 --> 01:05:43,950
Maybe.

649
01:05:46,020 --> 01:05:49,547
But by that time we'll be in Mexico.

650
01:05:57,820 --> 01:05:59,026
Romero!

651
01:05:59,180 --> 01:06:00,670
Companeros!

652
01:06:02,500 --> 01:06:04,104
The convoy left.

653
01:06:04,260 --> 01:06:07,025
Saddle up!
We do not wait Sartana to wait.

654
01:06:07,180 --> 01:06:09,547
Miguel. You and 3 men go over the hill.

655
01:06:09,700 --> 01:06:11,270
The rest come with me to the canyon.

656
01:06:52,180 --> 01:06:53,625
Is everything ready, Baxter?

657
01:06:53,780 --> 01:06:55,020
Yes, sir.

658
01:06:56,580 --> 01:06:59,982
I left the horses in the back,
nobody will see us leave.

659
01:07:00,380 --> 01:07:03,941
You know, it might be funny, but I'm
almost sorry to leave.

660
01:07:04,780 --> 01:07:05,702
I spent here 10 years?

661
01:07:05,940 --> 01:07:10,309
We had time to pick all the gold
from those idiots miners.

662
01:07:32,380 --> 01:07:35,429
Our work is completed, partner.

663
01:08:03,460 --> 01:08:05,747
Where I was, what I was...

664
01:08:05,900 --> 01:08:08,267
Why and how I was...

665
01:08:09,540 --> 01:08:11,463
Not far from the...

666
01:08:11,620 --> 01:08:14,988
 whisper of the water coming out...

667
01:08:15,220 --> 01:08:16,381
a cave.

668
01:08:23,660 --> 01:08:25,981
Gentlemen!
It's me you're looking for...

669
01:08:26,220 --> 01:08:27,301
or Sartana?

670
01:08:31,020 --> 01:08:32,784
This means, me.

671
01:08:33,020 --> 01:08:34,021
Is not it?

672
01:08:38,380 --> 01:08:39,620
Here I am.

673
01:08:41,460 --> 01:08:42,791
Here I am.

674
01:08:48,100 --> 01:08:49,147
Get off.

675
01:09:05,820 --> 01:09:07,902
Why were you looking over there?

676
01:09:26,260 --> 01:09:27,591
Here I am.

677
01:10:24,060 --> 01:10:24,868
Attention.

678
01:11:29,060 --> 01:11:32,462
The worm came out of his hole.
I'll have a drink.

679
01:11:45,540 --> 01:11:47,463
Come on! Where are you? I'm thirsty.

680
01:11:51,540 --> 01:11:54,066
Whre are you vermin?

681
01:11:54,220 --> 01:11:56,222
You don't need to talk like that.

682
01:11:56,940 --> 01:11:59,705
I'm tired of waiting for you.

683
01:12:18,140 --> 01:12:20,984
Thank you, partner.
Your plan worked well.

684
01:12:22,020 --> 01:12:23,385
And I want to thank you.

685
01:12:24,100 --> 01:12:27,468
For bringing me my share of the gold.

686
01:12:31,100 --> 01:12:34,866
No. I didn't bring you your share.

687
01:12:36,500 --> 01:12:39,025
You know, I still believe,
that I'm faster than you.

688
01:12:39,740 --> 01:12:41,583
And maybe you want to test it.

689
01:12:43,060 --> 01:12:44,061
OK.

690
01:12:44,380 --> 01:12:46,382
This is a good opportunity.

691
01:12:46,740 --> 01:12:49,107
I'd better warn you, Mantas.
I'm angry at you.

692
01:12:50,460 --> 01:12:51,746
You are dishonest.

693
01:12:55,980 --> 01:12:57,106
Thank you for the compliment.

694
01:12:58,580 --> 01:13:01,106
I am wondering whether
your hands are as fast...

695
01:13:01,260 --> 01:13:02,500
...as your mind.

696
01:13:04,260 --> 01:13:06,262
Now, listen to me.

697
01:13:07,500 --> 01:13:09,070
There are three of us.

698
01:13:09,580 --> 01:13:10,661
You,

699
01:13:11,460 --> 01:13:13,269
Keep an eye on the bread.

700
01:13:14,820 --> 01:13:18,142
You, count to three
and then take the gun.

701
01:13:19,260 --> 01:13:21,308
And I'm going to aim for your heart.

702
01:13:21,700 --> 01:13:23,589
This is a real duel.

703
01:13:25,740 --> 01:13:29,301
My gun against yours.
That one.

704
01:13:30,060 --> 01:13:30,902
Because...

705
01:13:31,140 --> 01:13:33,541
Where would you hide the gun?

706
01:13:33,940 --> 01:13:35,146
How do you know that there is no
one under the table?

707
01:13:37,780 --> 01:13:39,782
This time,
you have your boots on.

708
01:13:41,900 --> 01:13:43,629
- Pedro.
- One...

709
01:13:46,860 --> 01:13:47,861
Two...

710
01:14:50,020 --> 01:14:51,784
You're leaving, senor?

711
01:14:55,780 --> 01:14:59,865
Take care of these gentlemen.
They rather left us forever.

712
01:15:04,660 --> 01:15:08,062
That's for the solid coffins.

713
01:15:10,340 --> 01:15:12,229
Nad bury them deep
so they do not escape.

714
01:15:14,540 --> 01:15:16,224
Adiós, Sartana!

715
01:15:19,380 --> 01:15:20,461
You know what?

716
01:15:20,620 --> 01:15:23,942
Look, this place is a ghost town.
Why do not you leave?

717
01:15:25,700 --> 01:15:28,783
No. Mantas is now dead,
people will return.

718
01:15:29,300 --> 01:15:30,426
You decide where you're going?

719
01:15:30,860 --> 01:15:32,430
I have an important meeting.

720
01:15:33,420 --> 01:15:35,991
With someone who thinks is
always lucky.

721
01:17:04,900 --> 01:17:06,106
Do not shoot me, please!

722
01:17:07,500 --> 01:17:10,310
Sartana waits you at the saloon.

723
01:17:10,940 --> 01:17:13,307
Okay, Angelo, but better
if you're coming with me.

724
01:17:13,620 --> 01:17:15,463
I do not want you to miss this show.

725
01:18:00,100 --> 01:18:02,671
Very good.
As good as that of my mother.

726
01:18:18,900 --> 01:18:20,390
Sabata...

727
01:18:22,340 --> 01:18:23,341
Sartana is here.

728
01:18:41,100 --> 01:18:44,627
He is a true professional.
Never misses not a single meeting.

729
01:19:24,980 --> 01:19:27,460
Go back, the cup could break.

730
01:20:02,420 --> 01:20:04,104
Well, should I open it?

731
01:20:07,780 --> 01:20:08,986
My turn.

732
01:20:17,860 --> 01:20:19,464
Excellent quality.

733
01:20:20,580 --> 01:20:23,663
This is an excellent quality of the sand.

734
01:20:24,140 --> 01:20:26,302
You did not ask
what was the content.

735
01:20:26,740 --> 01:20:28,822
I already knew that there is sand in it.

736
01:20:34,380 --> 01:20:35,506
How about fifty per cent?

737
01:20:36,180 --> 01:20:38,228
I have nothing against that.

738
01:20:38,660 --> 01:20:40,991
If you are satisfied with it.
You got it.

739
01:20:42,980 --> 01:20:44,311
And this one too.

740
01:21:10,940 --> 01:21:12,430
Do not bluff me.

741
01:21:12,860 --> 01:21:14,430
I do not advise you.

742
01:21:14,900 --> 01:21:16,550
We do not play poker.

743
01:21:17,380 --> 01:21:19,189
I do not bluff.

744
01:21:28,620 --> 01:21:29,746
Neither do I.

745
01:21:40,660 --> 01:21:41,741
Bravo.

746
01:21:42,580 --> 01:21:44,947
Enjoy your cigar...

747
01:21:46,340 --> 01:21:49,105
Because this is the last one
you will ever smoke.

748
01:22:10,020 --> 01:22:11,385
You're not offended ...

749
01:22:17,540 --> 01:22:19,110
I did not. What about you?

750
01:22:58,180 --> 01:22:59,545
Out of bullets, right?

751
01:23:00,980 --> 01:23:02,345
No. I have one more, for you.

752
01:23:06,140 --> 01:23:06,948
Will ten.

753
01:23:07,260 --> 01:23:09,024
You're a scoundrel.

754
01:23:09,740 --> 01:23:10,582
You cheated.

755
01:23:10,780 --> 01:23:11,861
Yes, you're right.

756
01:23:12,180 --> 01:23:14,660
You know, I promised my mother...

757
01:23:15,060 --> 01:23:17,427
...not to deal with people like you..

758
01:23:17,980 --> 01:23:21,666
Now... Slowly go to your horse.

759
01:23:24,980 --> 01:23:28,063
And hold your hands away from everything.

760
01:23:30,700 --> 01:23:31,747
Hold it!

761
01:23:32,900 --> 01:23:34,823
Remove Winchester from the saddle.

762
01:23:35,740 --> 01:23:37,105
With the left hand.

763
01:23:41,180 --> 01:23:42,784
Take it to the barrel.

764
01:23:44,300 --> 01:23:47,668
There, like this.
Leave it there on the barrel.

765
01:23:54,100 --> 01:23:55,147
Now go.

766
01:24:10,380 --> 01:24:12,064
Hey. What are you doing?

767
01:24:16,380 --> 01:24:18,064
You forgot that I have this.

768
01:24:20,060 --> 01:24:22,028
You're too far away from me.

769
01:24:23,260 --> 01:24:24,500
You sure?

770
01:25:03,540 --> 01:25:04,701
You wanted it, right?

771
01:25:08,580 --> 01:25:09,945
A memory of his mother.

772
01:25:10,180 --> 01:25:12,182
Forget about him. Where is the gold?

773
01:25:20,500 --> 01:25:21,626
What are you doing?

774
01:25:32,740 --> 01:25:36,631
Oh, my... Do not tell me
that Angelo sat on it...

775
01:25:36,780 --> 01:25:38,270
...all this time.

776
01:25:39,220 --> 01:25:41,188
But he didn't know.

777
01:25:42,500 --> 01:25:44,867
Well, we did it.

778
01:25:45,860 --> 01:25:46,941
Half and half.

779
01:25:47,340 --> 01:25:50,389
You'll have to settle for $ 10,000.00

780
01:25:50,940 --> 01:25:52,385
My dear!

781
01:26:16,940 --> 01:26:18,704
This is not nice.

782
01:26:19,660 --> 01:26:23,745
You would surely lose the whole gold
if not the two of us.

783
01:26:24,060 --> 01:26:25,141
What do you mean "the two of us"?

784
01:26:38,700 --> 01:26:41,271
When he said "we",
he meant "us".

785
01:26:41,780 --> 01:26:44,943
Never trust the strangers, ma'am.
Never.

786
01:26:49,860 --> 01:26:51,669
Now what, my friend?

787
01:26:52,700 --> 01:26:54,270
Shall we?

788
01:26:57,700 --> 01:27:00,783
No one ever found out
where did you put the gun again?

789
01:27:00,940 --> 01:27:04,023
Of course not.
That is impossible.

790
01:27:04,500 --> 01:27:06,468
And what's with Trixie?

791
01:27:06,620 --> 01:27:08,543
She almost got us.

792
01:27:09,260 --> 01:27:10,227
<i>Women... </i>

793
01:27:10,380 --> 01:27:11,745
Women!

794
01:27:11,900 --> 01:27:15,666
You can only do one thing with them.
You love them, then leave them.

795
01:27:16,380 --> 01:27:17,541
Therefore, I never got married.

796
01:27:18,140 --> 01:27:19,551
Sabata...

797
01:27:19,780 --> 01:27:22,909
I'll bet you anything that
your mother was never married, either.

798
01:28:09,780 --> 01:28:12,509
Translated by YAFI.
JAGA BIALYSTOK!!!